QUES--> certain amount of money stashed, the only constraint stopping you from robbing each of them is that adjacent houses have 
security systems connected and it will automatically contact the police if two adjacent houses were broken into on the same night.
Given an integer array nums representing the amount of money of each house, return the maximum amount of money you can rob tonight 
without alerting the police.

What choices do you have?

Only two.

Choice 1: Rob this house

If you rob it,

i-1

cannot be robbed.

So after robbing house i, the best money becomes

nums[i] + best till (i-2)

because we skip one house.

Choice-2: Dont rob this one, and take the next one
If we don't rob house i

Nothing changes.

Best answer is simply

notTake = dp[i-1];

##########
Our recurrence becomes

dp[i] = max(take, notTake);

⭐ This is the entire DP relation.

TABULATION METHOD--> O(n) space

class Solution {
public:
    int rob(vector<int>& nums) {

        int n = nums.size();

        if(n == 1)
            return nums[0];

        vector<int> dp(n);

        dp[0] = nums[0];
        dp[1] = max(nums[0], nums[1]);

        for(int i = 2; i < n; i++)
        {
            int take = nums[i] + dp[i-2];
            int notTake = dp[i-1];

            dp[i] = max(take, notTake);
        }

        return dp[n-1];
    }
};

NEXT FINALLY THE OPTIMIZED METHOD WOULD BE--> 
When computing dp[i], which values do we need?

Only:

dp[i-1]
dp[i-2]

Nothing else.

We'll store only two variables.

prev2 = dp[i-2]
prev1 = dp[i-1]

Think of them like this:

prev2  prev1   curr
  |       |      |
dp[i-2] dp[i-1] dp[i]

class Solution {
public:
    int rob(vector<int>& nums) {

        int n = nums.size();

        if(n == 1)
            return nums[0];

        int prev2 = nums[0];
        int prev1 = max(nums[0], nums[1]);

        for(int i = 2; i < n; i++)
        {
            int take = nums[i] + prev2;
            int notTake = prev1;

            int curr = max(take, notTake);

            // Shift the window
            prev2 = prev1;
            prev1 = curr;
        }

        return prev1;
    }
};
